node.text:
I recorded some stages of the painting process to talk a little about the similarities of painting textures digitally and painting a statue. I remember when I was starting to paint textures in 3D very often my textures ended up muddy and the models ended up looking fake. One of the things I learned throughout the years is that simple is usually better. Relying on the sculpt to drive color and details will make the result better. 
Finding a strong base color is the foundation of everything. On top of the base color we can paint cavities with washes and highlights with dry brushing, similar to cavity and curvature masking digitally. A mix between hot and cold colors between the base, cavity and highlights usually gives the best results. 
I used acrylic paints, paint brushes and airbrushing. Let me know if you have any questions. 👍🏻
Painting is one of my favorite part of the process to do, it just takes a long time, like everything else 😊

🔺Metroid

——
For those who read the description this is one of many projects that i started but ended up losing steam and put on the corner to focus on other projects. I have a lot of people asking me what to do when the motivation goes away, it’s ok to do that, take a break but force yourself to get back to it later. That’s why i end up not posting wip shots online, try to avoid the feeling of the “work being done” by posting it online and get back to it to finish it properly later. Have fun! 🍻
